# Section Components Guidelines

This folder contains **landing page section components** - larger compositional components that make up the distinct sections of the landing page.

---

## Purpose

Section components represent major visual blocks of the landing page:
- Hero Section
- Features Section
- About Section
- Testimonials Section
- Pricing Section
- CTA Section
- FAQ Section

---

## Core Principles

### Composition Over Complexity

Sections should **compose UI components**, not duplicate them:

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Composes UI components
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';
import { Container } from '@/components/ui/Container';
import { Heading, Text } from '@/components/ui/Typography';

export function HeroSection() {
  return (
    <section className="py-20">
      <Container>
        <Heading level={1}>Welcome to Coddlers</Heading>
        <Text>Your subtitle here</Text>
        <Button variant="primary">Get Started</Button>
      </Container>
    </section>
  );
}
```

### Content Separation

Keep content data separate from presentation:

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Content is externalized
const features = [
  { icon: 'code', title: 'Fast Development', description: '...' },
  { icon: 'shield', title: 'Secure by Default', description: '...' },
];

export function FeaturesSection() {
  return (
    <section>
      {features.map((feature) => (
        <FeatureCard key={feature.title} {...feature} />
      ))}
    </section>
  );
}
```

Consider moving content to `constants/` for larger datasets.

