## Responsive Design Requirements

All sections must be responsive across breakpoints:

```tsx
<section className={cn(
  // Mobile first
  'py-12 px-4',
  // Tablet
  'md:py-16 md:px-6',
  // Desktop
  'lg:py-24 lg:px-8'
)}>
```

### Grid Patterns

```tsx
// Feature cards grid
<div className={cn(
  'grid gap-6',
  'grid-cols-1',           // Mobile: 1 column
  'md:grid-cols-2',        // Tablet: 2 columns
  'lg:grid-cols-3'         // Desktop: 3 columns
)}>
```

---

## Animation Guidelines

Use Framer Motion for scroll-triggered and entrance animations:

```tsx
import { motion } from 'framer-motion';

// Fade up animation
const fadeUpVariants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 20 },
  visible: { 
    opacity: 1, 
    y: 0,
    transition: { duration: 0.5, ease: 'easeOut' }
  },
};

// Stagger children
const staggerContainer = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0 },
  visible: {
    opacity: 1,
    transition: { staggerChildren: 0.1 },
  },
};
```

### Performance Considerations

- Use `whileInView` for scroll-triggered animations
- Add `viewport={{ once: true }}` to animate only once
- Keep animations subtle (< 500ms duration)
- Use `transform` and `opacity` for GPU-accelerated animations

---

## Section Naming Convention

- Use descriptive names: `HeroSection`, `FeaturesSection`
- Suffix with "Section" for clarity
- File names match component names: `HeroSection.tsx`

---

## Section IDs for Navigation

Add `id` attributes for smooth scrolling navigation:

```tsx
<section id="features" className="...">
  {/* Content */}
</section>
```

This enables navigation links like:
```tsx
<a href="#features">Features</a>
```

---

## Checklist for New Sections

- [ ] Uses semantic `<section>` element
- [ ] Has unique `id` for navigation
- [ ] Responsive across all breakpoints
- [ ] Composes UI components (doesn't duplicate)
- [ ] Content is separated from presentation
- [ ] Animations are performant and accessible
- [ ] Follows consistent spacing patterns
